Starbucks App Customer Rewards Program¶

MSCA 31008 | Data Mining Principles | Professor U. Pamuksuz | Team Project¶

Business problem:

Identify the profile of the ideal customer (and the worst customer) in the dataset.

Starbucks managemnent wants to know who are our best and worst customers and the effect of offers on them.

The following problems are expected to solve:

  • identfy the group of best customers and continiue to target them
  • identify the group of worst customers (less active and less responsive to offers) and develop additional strategies for targeting them
  • compare best customers' group in general and best customers in terms of offer response
  • design an ideal offer

This work should be done in collaboration with PCA and clustering algorithms.

plt.title("Spending by age group and number of bogo offers")
Out[128]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Spending by age group and number of bogo offers')

This is also very interesting. We can see that customers between 20 and 29 years old decrease their spending amount with the increase of the number of discount offers. This is pretty contrintuitive. This age group shold not be targeted too frequently.

At the same time, the same age group has a significant response rate to bogo offers. The more they receive - the more they spend.

Hence, we identified a group of customers, which reacts very differently on various types of offers. We definitely need to tune parameters of the program for this group.

Consculsion: we completed a pretty comprehensive analysis of spending by Starbucks customers, combining them simultanious by different parameters - age and income group, type and number of offers, and gender.

As a result, now we can clearly identify several categories of our best and "worst" groups of customers. In turn, it will allow Starbucks to continue its current strategies for responsive customers and review own marketing strategies for customers, who are not that active.
